# ML / Deep Learning artifacts
# IMPORTANT: Model weights and large binary checkpoints are NEVER committed
*.pt
*.pth
*.ckpt
*.safetensors
*.bin
*.onnx
*.pb
*.tflite
# Common checkpoint / weight naming patterns (extra safety)
**/best*.pt
**/last*.pt
**/model_*.pt
**/checkpoint*.pt

# Experiment results policy (updated to match user request):
# We COMMIT experimental OUTPUTS and results for reproducibility:
#   - metrics_*.csv / *.json, predictions, pcc curves, training history
#   - plots and figures from experiments
#   - split summaries, args, configs
# Large RAW DATASETS and model weights stay out (see below).

# NO blanket ignore for outputs/ or runs/ — we want the result files.
# (Individual heavy binaries inside them are still blocked by *.pt rules above.)

# Large / problematic datasets (do NOT commit full copies)
# MSTAR: 5000+ SAR images, bad for git (many small files)
data/MSTAR/
**/MSTAR/
# CIFAR-10: large tarball + extracted, duplicated across many resnet projects
**/cifar-10-batches-py/
**/cifar-10-python.tar.gz

# Archives and zips (these are backups of projects)
*.zip
zip0/

# Lightning AI specific
.lightning*
*.lightning_upload

# Battery raw data: the extracted .mat files (~54MB total) ARE committed
# because they are the core dataset for the SOH experiments and are reasonable size.
# (No ignore rule needed — they are already tracked.)

# Other temp
*.tmp
*.temp

